    "\"EHSL\" refers to the English High School Listening Test we collected, containing long/short speech types.‡ indicates that this model employs enormous or unknown data during training.",
    "Effectiveness of Training Strategy: We examine the impact of different training strategies on model performance by presenting three distinct model variants in Table 8.",
    "The comparative analysis between model variant (a) and variants (b), (c) and (d) first reveals that the tri-phase training approach employed in the model (a) facilitates noticeable enhancements across a range of multimodal benchmarks.",
    "This underscores the benefit of incorporating specialized training phases for cross-modality data, affirming the strategic advantage of engaging training experts in the process.",
    "Further analysis shows that training MoE with identical configurations (see pure models in Table 8) could result in a negligible performance increase compared to a singleexpert approach, as evidenced by models (b), (c), (d), (e), and (f)."
